						<summary>

						<p>Slab (another) fixed in to the floor in the <hi rend="italic">mukhamaṇḍapa</hi> of the Aṅkāḷamma temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1608 (expired) Krōdhana, Āśvija śu. 12,</hi> corresponding to 1685 A.D., September 29, Tuesday.</p>						

						<p>It records a grant of land made by the reḍḍi and Karaṇam of the village to the stone masons <hi rend="italic">(Kāśa)</hi> Bālaya, Pāpaya and Koṇḍaya.</p>						

						</summary>
